    "Thursday April 51962 The Universitys 1962 Weil Lecture i Atomic Energy A Problem For Citizens Too A Huge Potential For Evil Or Good The Weil Lecture on American Citizenship delivered at the Uni versity on March 29 1982 Ir Baxter former president of Wil liams College is Senior Fellow of He is the author of Scientists Against Time which won a Pulitzer Prize in 1947 and during World War II he was deputy director of the Office of Strategic Services By JAMES P BAXTER 111 In 1909 the year after the Great English physicist Ruther ford won the Nobel Prize for his work in radioactivity his fellow countryman William Watson pub lished a sonnet that sums up in fourteen lines the dilemma of the citizen of the nuclear age It con tains the first reference 1 have seen in verse to atomic fission and it employs a figure of speech which lias since become familiar to all of you What is that fieriest sub stance found of late That cousin to the uranium of the sun Should be the cause of all that we have done And dreamed and been A source of Love and Hate Virtue and Valouryea and"
